Family dynamics. ~
•
•
One of my favorite things about taking pictures of my girls is seeing how their different personalities really come through. Mieka has always been more affectionate. She basically tries to get as close as possible to me. Kylie on the other hand has always been much more quiet about showing her love, so she will always position herself about a foot away. It’s something I never really noticed until I started  taking pictures of them. Have you ever had a similar experience or noticed any quirks about your dog or animal from a photo?

"Independent yet Attached”
•
•
I don’t think there is a better expression that could quickly sum up Kylie’s personality. She’s incredibly strong willed & fiercely independent (2 traits that made bonding with her hard at first), but she’s also grown into a very loyal & loving girl. She’s not affectionate in the traditional sense, she’s never going to be a cuddler or kisser— she has her own brand of love on her own terms.  I’ve come to appreciate the quiet way in which she shows love— it’s subtle. Most people probably wouldn’t even notice, but those small things mean everything to me. ~
